**Checklist structure (ordered):**
1. Pre-flight: clean tree, on the release commit, pull latest.
2. Green-gate (run, expect all green/exit 0):
   - `go build ./...`
   - `go test ./...` (equivalently `make test`)
   - `make lint` (the lint target EXISTS — `Makefile:13-15`: `gofmt -l cmd
     internal` must be empty + `go vet ./...`)
   - `make docs-reality` (hand-written-doc/CLI drift guard)
   - `make reconcile` (docs-reality + docs-check holistic gate)
   - `make dogfood-audit` (repo dogfood completeness: run refs / gate records /
     pushed refs — appropriate as a release gate for this dogfooded repo)
   - State the expected green result for each.
3. Pick version + update CHANGELOG: choose `v1.0.0`; change CHANGELOG's
   `## [v1.0.0] — Unreleased` heading (`CHANGELOG.md:23`) to
   `## [v1.0.0] — <release date>`; commit the CHANGELOG edit.
4. Build the stamped binary: `make build VERSION=v1.0.0`; verify
   `./bin/etude --version` prints `etude v1.0.0` (REFERENCE README `## Releasing`
   for why/how — do not restate ldflags). [Verified: prints `etude v1.0.0`.]
5. Cut the tag — HUMAN action. The doc states HOW (e.g. `git tag v1.0.0 <sha>`
   then push the tag) but the operator performs it; kb0.4 does NOT cut the tag.
6. Sync etude run data — the refs caveat (below) as an explicit step.
7. Pointer to `docs/plans/product/V1-SCOPE.md` for in-scope vs deferred.

**Sync/refs caveat (VERIFIED accurate):** `refs/etude/*` do NOT travel with a
plain `git push`/`git fetch` — those move only `refs/heads/*` and `refs/tags/*`
by default (`docs/sync.md:7-10`). `etude init` writes the fetch refspec
`+refs/etude/*:refs/etude/*` and push refspec `refs/etude/*:refs/etude/*` into
git config (`docs/init.md:26-31`) so a subsequent plain `git fetch` picks up the
namespace. `etude sync` passes refspecs explicitly and works WHETHER OR NOT init
ran (`docs/sync.md:30,127-132`). Handoff wording: "A fresh clone or CI will not
see captured run data after a normal `git clone`/`git pull`. Either run
`etude init` (registers the `refs/etude/*` refspec so plain fetches pick it up)
and/or run `etude sync` (explicit push/fetch of `refs/etude/*`). See
[docs/sync.md](docs/sync.md)."

